		"description": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-6279ed4a-7fff-d888-30df-67572cca37e8\" dir=\"ltr\">Also at 18th level, when you score a critical hit, you can choose to spend two artifact charges to impose one of the following conditions on the target, based on your affliction:</p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Unmoored:</strong> Confused</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>Paranoid:</strong> Frightened</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>Troubled:</strong>&nbsp; Unconscious - the target is asleep and wakes if it takes any damage or an action is taken to shake it awake.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>Fettered:</strong> Encumbered</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><strong>Gravebound:</strong> Blinded</li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">The condition lasts for one minute, but the target can make a Constitution save against your spell save DC at the end of each of its turns, ending the condition early on a success.</p>",
